GOOD HUMOR CORPORATION OF AMERICA, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. BLUE BIRD ICE CREAM AND CHARLOTTE RUSSE, Inc., Defendant-Appellee. No. 455. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. July 5, 1933. Thomas G. Haight, of Jersey City, N. J., Samuel E. Darby, Jr., of New York City, and John E. Robb, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellant. W. Lee Helms, of New York City, for appellee. John P. Neary, Ramsay Hoguet, and Theodore E. Simonton, all of New York City, for National Dairy Products Corporation.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (1 P. Supp. 850) affirmed on opinion below.
